Step 23 — GitHub Actions: Backend CI/CD
.github/workflows/backend-ci.yml
yamlname: Backend CI/CD

on:
  push:
    branches: [main, develop]
    paths:
      - 'backend/**'
      - '.github/workflows/backend-ci.yml'
  pull_request:
    branches: [main, develop]
    paths:
      - 'backend/**'

jobs:
  test:
    name: Test
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    defaults:
      run:
        working-directory: ./backend

    services:
      postgres:
        image: postgres:15
        env:
          POSTGRES_DB: testdb
          POSTGRES_USER: testuser
          POSTGRES_PASSWORD: testpass
        ports:
          - 5432:5432
        options: >-
          --health-cmd pg_isready
          --health-interval 10s
          --health-timeout 5s
          --health-retries 5

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Set up Java 17
        uses: actions/setup-java@v4
        with:
          java-version: '17'
          distribution: 'temurin'
          cache: maven

      - name: Run tests
        env:
          SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE: test
          DATABASE_URL: jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/testdb
          DATABASE_USERNAME: testuser
          DATABASE_PASSWORD: testpass
          JWT_SECRET: test-secret-key-at-least-256-bits-long-1234567890
          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: test
          AT_API_KEY: test
          AT_USERNAME: sandbox
          PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY: test
          PAYSTACK_WEBHOOK_SECRET: test
        run: mvn test

  deploy-dev:
    name: Deploy to Development
    needs: test
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/develop' && github.event_name == 'push'

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Railway CLI
        run: npm install -g @railway/cli

      - name: Deploy to Railway (dev)
        env:
          RAILWAY_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.RAILWAY_TOKEN_DEV }}
        run: railway up --service hardware-assistant-dev

  deploy-prod:
    name: Deploy to Production
    needs: test
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main' && github.event_name == 'push'

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Railway CLI
        run: npm install -g @railway/cli

      - name: Deploy to Railway (prod)
        env:
          RAILWAY_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.RAILWAY_TOKEN_PROD }}
        run: railway up --service hardware-assistant-prod
Step 24 — GitHub Actions: Frontend CI/CD
.github/workflows/frontend-ci.yml
yamlname: Frontend CI/CD

on:
  push:
    branches: [main, develop]
    paths:
      - 'frontend/**'
      - '.github/workflows/frontend-ci.yml'
  pull_request:
    branches: [main, develop]
    paths:
      - 'frontend/**'

jobs:
  build:
    name: Build & Lint
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    defaults:
      run:
        working-directory: ./frontend

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Setup Node.js
        uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: '20'
          cache: 'npm'
          cache-dependency-path: frontend/package-lock.json

      - name: Install dependencies
        run: npm ci

      - name: Lint
        run: npm run lint

      - name: Build (dev)
        if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/develop'
        env:
          VITE_API_BASE_URL: ${{ secrets.DEV_API_BASE_URL }}
        run: npm run build

      - name: Build (prod)
        if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'
        env:
          VITE_API_BASE_URL: ${{ secrets.PROD_API_BASE_URL }}
        run: npm run build

  deploy-vercel-dev:
    name: Deploy to Vercel (Dev Preview)
    needs: build
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/develop'

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Deploy to Vercel
        uses: amondnet/vercel-action@v25
        with:
          vercel-token: ${{ secrets.VERCEL_TOKEN }}
          vercel-org-id: ${{ secrets.VERCEL_ORG_ID }}
          vercel-project-id: ${{ secrets.VERCEL_PROJECT_ID }}
          working-directory: ./frontend

  deploy-vercel-prod:
    name: Deploy to Vercel (Production)
    needs: build
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Deploy to Vercel (Prod)
        uses: amondnet/vercel-action@v25
        with:
          vercel-token: ${{ secrets.VERCEL_TOKEN }}
          vercel-org-id: ${{ secrets.VERCEL_ORG_ID }}
          vercel-project-id: ${{ secrets.VERCEL_PROJECT_ID }}
          vercel-args: '--prod'
          working-directory: ./frontend
```

### Step 25 — GitHub Secrets to Configure

Add these in GitHub → Settings → Secrets and Variables → Actions:

| Secret Name | Description |
|---|---|
| `RAILWAY_TOKEN_DEV` | Railway dev environment token |
| `RAILWAY_TOKEN_PROD` | Railway prod environment token |
| `VERCEL_TOKEN` | Vercel API token |
| `VERCEL_ORG_ID` | Vercel org ID |
| `VERCEL_PROJECT_ID` | Vercel project ID |
| `DEV_API_BASE_URL` | Dev backend URL |
| `PROD_API_BASE_URL` | Prod backend URL |

### Step 26 — Railway Environment Variables (set in Railway dashboard)

For each Railway service, add:
```
SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=prod
DATABASE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://...
DATABASE_USERNAME=...
DATABASE_PASSWORD=...
JWT_SECRET=<generate with: openssl rand -base64 64>
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
AT_API_KEY=...
AT_USERNAME=...
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
PAYSTACK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=...
```

---

## PART 5: BUSINESS MODEL

### Step 27 — Subscription Pricing (Paystack NGN)

| Plan | Price/Month | Analyses/Month | SMS Included |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Free** | ₦0 | 3 | No |
| **Starter** | ₦2,500 | 20 | 5 SMS |
| **Growth** | ₦7,500 | 100 | 20 SMS |
| **Pro** | ₦15,000 | Unlimited | 50 SMS |

### Step 28 — Monthly Cost Breakdown (at 100 active users)

| Service | Estimated Cost |
|---|---|
| Railway (backend) | $5–20/month |
| Railway (PostgreSQL) | $5/month |
| Vercel (frontend) | Free–$20/month |
| Anthropic API | ~$0.015/analysis × 500 analyses = ~$7.50 |
| Africa's Talking SMS | ~₦20/SMS × 200 SMS = ₦4,000 (~$2.50) |
| **Total** | **~$40–55/month** |

Break-even: Just 3 Starter subscribers (₦7,500/mo = ~$4.50) covers hosting. Every Growth/Pro subscriber is profit.

---

## PART 6: PRODUCTION READINESS CHECKLIST
```
SECURITY
□ JWT secret is ≥256-bit random string (openssl rand -base64 64)
□ All secrets are in env vars, NOT in code or git
□ .gitignore includes .env* files
□ CORS restricted to actual frontend domain in production
□ Paystack webhook signature verification enabled
□ Passwords BCrypt-hashed (cost factor 10+)
□ Input validation on all endpoints

DATABASE
□ Flyway migrations run on startup
□ DB connection pool sized appropriately (Hikari)
□ DB credentials rotated from defaults
□ Backups enabled on Railway managed DB

DEVOPS
□ main branch protected (PR required)
□ CI passes before merge allowed
□ Separate Railway services for dev/prod
□ Separate Vercel environments for dev/prod
□ Environment variables set per environment

MONITORING
□ /actuator/health endpoint accessible
□ Logging level WARN in production
□ Error responses never leak stack traces

FRONTEND
□ API base URL from env var (never hardcoded)
□ 401 responses auto-redirect to login
□ Loading states on all async operations
□ Error messages shown to user

DAY-BY-DAY EXECUTION PLAN
DayTasksDay 1Backend scaffold, DB migrations, Auth (register/login), JWT workingDay 2Merchant profile, AI service, Analysis generation + historyDay 3SMS service, Payment webhook, Admin controllerDay 4Frontend: Auth pages, Dashboard, Profile, Analysis pageDay 5Admin dashboard, CI/CD pipelines, Deploy to Railway + Vercel, smoke test
